<p><b>Criminal justice</b> is the system of practices and institutions of <a href="Government" title="Government">governments</a> directed at upholding <a href="Social_control" title="Social control">social control</a>, <a href="Deterrence_(legal)" title="Deterrence (legal)">deterring</a> and mitigating <a href="Crime" title="Crime">crime</a>, or sanctioning those who violate <a href="Law" title="Law">laws</a> with criminal penalties and <a href="Rehabilitation_(penology)" title="Rehabilitation (penology)">rehabilitation</a> efforts. Those accused of crime have <a href="Rights_of_the_accused" title="Rights of the accused" class="mw-redirect">protections</a> against abuse of investigatory and prosecution powers.</p>
